= Internal Factions of the SPD

{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="The Modernisers are neutral on reunification, preferring a slower transition and reunification to prevent unmitigated consequences.">Modernisers</span>!} Strength: [+ moderniser_strength : strength +], Dissent: [+ moderniser_dissent : dissent +]

{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="The Ostpolitikers push for a swift reunificaton on equal grounds, rather than the absorption of one over another and are the most friendly towards the East.">Ostpolitikers</span>!} Strength: [+ ostpolitiker_strength : strength +], Dissent: [+ ostpolitiker_dissent : dissent +]

{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="Labour seeks to advance worker rights and protect workers, no matter how reunification goes.">Labour</span>!} Strength: [+ labour_strength : strength +], Dissent: [+ labour_dissent : dissent +]

{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="The Atlanticists advocate for a reunified Germany that remains in NATO and is fully aligned with the West.">Atlanticists</span>!} Strength: [+ atlanticist_strength : strength +], Dissent: [+ atlanticist_dissent : dissent +]


@economy

= Economy

{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="The Reichsbanner Schwarz-Rot-Gold is a popular organization for defending democracy, mostly affiliated with the SPD.">Reichsbanner</span>!} Strength: [+ rb_strength_2 +] thousand

Reichsbanner Militarization: [+ rb_militancy : militancy +]

